MEMBERS OF COCOON.

278
00:16:07,125 --> 00:16:08,750
THE COCOON REPRESENTATIVES
CAME EARLY,

279
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:10,583
PRESUMABLY TO ATTEND
THE SECRET TALKS

280
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:12,166
- WHAT'S WRONG?
- WHICH CERTAIN COUNTRIES

281
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:14,791
ARE SAID TO HOLD PRIOR TO THE
OFFICIAL START OF THE SUMMIT.

282
00:16:14,875 --> 00:16:17,791
WHEN ASKED IF THIS WAS THE CASE,
COCOON DECLINED TO COMMENT.

283
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:29,208
- Chikage: KUZUHA. IS THAT
FORBIDDEN BLING I SEE?

284
00:16:29,291 --> 00:16:31,958
- CLASS REPRESENTATIVES SHOULD
BE ALLOWED CERTAIN PERKS.

285
00:16:32,041 --> 00:16:33,333
- HUH?

286
00:16:33,416 --> 00:16:36,791
WHAT THE HECK? GET A
LOAD OF MINI MUSSOLINI.

287
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:39,166
- Chikage: HELLO?
- SORRY.

288
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:40,916
- Kuzuha: EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

289
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:44,625
- HEY. MAYBE THIS IS
A STUPID QUESTION.

290
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:46,916
BUT WHAT'S COCOON ABOUT?

291
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,916
- WELL, THAT'S PRETTY
DARN RANDOM.

292
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,333
- IT'S JUST,

293
00:16:50,416 --> 00:16:52,500
THEY WERE TALKING ABOUT IT
ON THE NEWS THIS MORNING,

294
00:16:52,583 --> 00:16:53,750
AND I WAS WONDERING.

295
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:55,458
- I FORGOT!

296
00:16:55,541 --> 00:16:57,666
SUMMONING SYNDROME DID A
REAL NUMBER ON YOUR MEMORY

297
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,541
OF HOW THINGS WORK
AROUND HERE, HUH?

298
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:02,333
I CAN'T EVEN IMAGINE HOW TRIPPY
IT MUST BE TO HAVE AMNESIA

299
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:04,250
AND YOU HARDLY EVER
TALK ABOUT IT.

300
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:06,791
- I GUESS. THEY'RE THE BEST
OF THE BEST OF US.

301
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:10,250
AND AS SUCH, THEY HELP
PRESERVE THE GLOBAL PEACE.

302
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:14,375
COCOON STANDS FOR "CHILDREN
OF CROSS OVER OTHER NATIONS".

303
00:17:14,458 --> 00:17:16,458
YOU SEE, IT'S AN ACRONYM.

304
00:17:16,541 --> 00:17:19,916
MEMBERS OF COCOON
ARE STRONG. CRAZILY SO.

305
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,125
EACH ONE IS MORE POWERFUL

306
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:24,541
THAN THEIR NATION'S
COMBINED MILITARY MIGHT.

307
00:17:24,625 --> 00:17:26,000
AS THE LEADERS OF BABEL,

308
00:17:26,083 --> 00:17:28,708
IT'S UP TO THEM TO SUPERVISE
AND EDUCATE KIDS LIKE US

309
00:17:28,791 --> 00:17:30,583
WHO'VE RETURNED
FROM OTHER WORLDS.

310
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:34,666
AND TO HELP KEEP THIS WORLD AS
PEACEFUL AS IT CAN POSSIBLY BE.

311
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:36,458
KEEPING THE PEACE IS THE
REASON THEY SEND US HERE

312
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:38,208
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

313
00:17:38,291 --> 00:17:40,208
TO MAKE SURE OUR ABILITIES
AREN'T EXPLOITED

314
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:42,750
BY THOSE WHO'D LOOK
TO GAIN FROM THEM.

315
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:45,666
AND, SO THAT BABEL CAN DEPLOY
US TO QUASH WHATEVER WARS

316
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:50,208
OR REGIONAL CONFLICTS MIGHT
FLARE UP AROUND THE GLOBE.

317
00:17:50,291 --> 00:17:51,583
- Cocoon male 4A: LOOK.

318
00:17:51,666 --> 00:17:53,291
I DON'T SEE THE NEED FOR US
TO CONVERGE LIKE THIS

319
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:56,791
JUST BECAUSE SOME "HERO"
HAS STEPPED ONTO THE BOARD.

320
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:58,208
- Cocoon female A:
IT'S POINTLESS.

321
00:17:58,291 --> 00:18:00,666
WE'LL SEE EACH OTHER
AT THE OFFICIAL SUMMIT ANYHOW.

322
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:03,333
DOES THIS REALLY MERIT
A CLANDESTINE MEETING?

323
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:04,875
- Cocoon female B:
SO THE NORN CHECK DETERMINED

324
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:07,166
THIS GUY IS A "TRUE HERO," HUH?

325
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,958
HOW VERY MELODRAMATIC.

326
00:18:09,041 --> 00:18:12,250
AS THOUGH WE'RE MERE INTERLOPERS
KEEPING THE THRONE WARM FOR HIM.

327
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:14,125
DOES THAT BOTHER ANYONE ELSE?

328
00:18:14,208 --> 00:18:15,583
- Cocoon male B:
WHAT IF THAT'S ALL WE ARE?

329
00:18:17,208 --> 00:18:18,916
PRETENDERS TO THE THRONE.

330
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,708
EVERY LAST ONE OF US.

331
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:22,958
- Cocoon male C: YOU CAN'T GIVE
IN TO THOUGHTS OF SELF-DOUBT.

332
00:18:23,041 --> 00:18:25,791
WHAT MATTERS IS THAT WE ACT IN
ACCORDANCE WITH OUR BELIEFS.

333
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:28,125
WE MUST KEEP TO THE PATH
WE'VE CHOSEN.

334
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:30,500
- Cocoon female C: SO, WHAT
DO YOU MAKE OF THIS HERO?

335
00:18:30,583 --> 00:18:33,125
- Kyoya: I'VE SEEN A
BIT OF WHAT HE CAN DO.

336
00:18:33,208 --> 00:18:37,041
BUT AS OF YET, I CAN'T SPEAK
TO HIS FULL POTENTIAL.

337
00:18:37,125 --> 00:18:40,416
FOR NOW, I'LL WATCH HIM FROM
HIS SPOT IN THE CLASS B FISHBOWL

338
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:43,625
AND DECIDE WHETHER HE'S WORTHY
OF JOINING OUR RANKS.

339
00:18:43,708 --> 00:18:45,583
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER,

340
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:49,500
I DO NOT THINK AKATSUKI OUSAWA
SHALL PROVE A DISAPPOINTMENT.

341
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:54,458
- I GET IT NOW.

342
00:18:54,541 --> 00:18:57,625
- Kuzuha: I'M A LITTLE WORRIED
ABOUT YOUR BROTHER, MIU.

343
00:18:57,708 --> 00:19:00,708
I DON'T KNOW, SOMETHING SEEMS
OFF ABOUT HIM. HE'S TENSE.

344
00:19:00,791 --> 00:19:02,166
DO YOU KNOW IF HE'S
BEEN STRESSING OUT

345
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,000
ABOUT ANYTHING RECENTLY?

346
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:05,541
- KIND OF.

347
00:19:05,625 --> 00:19:07,791
AS SOON AS THEY MENTIONED
THOSE COCOON GUYS ON THE NEWS,

348
00:19:07,875 --> 00:19:10,166
HE CLAMMED UP
AND GOT ALL WEIRD.

349
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:11,750
- GUESS HE'S GOT BEEF WITH THEM.

350
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:13,708
I'M NOT USED TO HIM
KEEPING STUFF TO HIMSELF.

351
00:19:14,583 --> 00:19:16,166
AKATSUKI IS LIKE...

352
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:19,250
LIKE A BIG DUMB OPEN BOOK, ALL
DOUBLE-SPACED AND OBNOXIOUS.

353
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:21,250
