ABOUT DOING THE NASTY.

364
00:19:42,166 --> 00:19:43,333
- ( she gasps )

365
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:45,666
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I'M NOT THINKING THAT!

366
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,500
WHY WOULD I THINK THAT
ABOUT MY BROTHER?

367
00:19:50,583 --> 00:19:52,083
BESIDES, EVEN IF
WE WEREN'T RELATED,

368
00:19:52,166 --> 00:19:53,958
I THINK HE LIKES SOMEBODY.

369
00:19:54,041 --> 00:19:55,416
AND EVEN IF WE
WEREN'T AND HE DIDN'T,

370
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:57,791
I DON'T LIKE HIM LIKE
THAT, SO WHATEVER!

371
00:19:57,875 --> 00:19:59,458
ON A TOTALLY UNRELATED NOTE,

372
00:19:59,541 --> 00:20:01,583
COULD I MAYBE GET THE TWO OF
YOU TO GO SHOPPING WITH ME

373
00:20:01,666 --> 00:20:03,500
SOMETIME IN THE NEAR FUTURE?

374
00:20:04,625 --> 00:20:06,208
- SURE THING.
SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

375
00:20:06,291 --> 00:20:07,958
- SHOPPING? FOR WHAT?

376
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:10,291
- UH, SOME BRAS?

377
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:11,833
- COUNT ME IN!

378
00:20:11,916 --> 00:20:14,416
